Firefighters are still struggling to contain a blaze at The Craggs just outside Plettenberg Bay. CAPE TOWN - Firefighters are still struggling to contain a blaze at The Craggs just outside Plettenberg Bay.More than 3,000 hectares of land have been destroyed in the Garden Route National Park.The fire first broke out about eight days ago.Working on Fire s Lauren Howard says: There s currently an active fire line on the north-western flank of the fire and firefighters are trying to contain it. Mountain to Ocean Forestry as well as Working on Fire teams have moved to secure plantation with fire bricks. The teams are also fighting to contain a fire north of the N2. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)